## How rubrics map to layers

Layer 4 (rubrics) is **not** Layer 1 (design-system source content). Layer 1 describes what "good" IS — tokens, principles, brand rules. Layer 4 encodes **checks against** that content: how we verify a work item upholds it. A rubric points at Layer 1 source (e.g., a tokens reference) and asks criterion-by-criterion whether the work under review complies. Never duplicate Layer 1 content inside a rubric; cite it.

